msgid "chaotic\\_pfc.dynamics.lyapunov"
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.dynamics.lyapunov:2 of
msgid "lyapunov.py"
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.dynamics.lyapunov:3 of
msgid ""
"Lyapunov exponent computation for the Hénon map (2-D) and the Hénon map "
"with a pole filter (4-D)."
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.dynamics.lyapunov:6 of
msgid "4-D system:"
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.dynamics.lyapunov:7 of
msgid ""
"x₁[n+1] = α − x₃[n]² + β·x₂[n] x₂[n+1] = x₁[n] x₃[n+1] = b₀·(α − x₃[n]² +"
" β·x₂[n]) + a₁·x₃[n] + a₂·x₄[n] x₄[n+1] = x₃[n]"
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.dynamics.lyapunov:12 of
msgid "where b = [b₀, 0, 0] and a = −[1, −2r·cos(w₀), r²]  (pole-filter coeffs)."
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.dynamics.lyapunov:14 of
msgid "2-D system:"
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.dynamics.lyapunov:15 of
msgid "x₁[n+1] = α − x₁[n]² + β·x₂[n] x₂[n+1] = x₁[n]"
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.dynamics.lyapunov:18 of
msgid "Two flavours of computation are provided:"
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.dynamics.lyapunov:20 of
msgid ""
"``lyapunov_max`` / ``lyapunov_henon2d`` — single perturbed initial "
"condition, returning one estimate of the spectrum."
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.dynamics.lyapunov:22 of
msgid ""
"``lyapunov_max_ensemble`` / ``lyapunov_henon2d_ensemble`` — full "
"experimental protocol: sample N_ci initial conditions uniformly around "
"the fixed point (±``perturbation``), compute the spectrum for each, and "
"aggregate statistics. Results can be exported to CSV via "
":meth:`EnsembleResult.to_csv`."
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.dynamics.lyapunov:29 of
msgid "Implementation note"
msgstr ""

#: chaotic_pfc.dynamics.lyapunov:30 of
msgid ""
"The 2-D and 4-D variants share the same QR/Gram-Schmidt loop; the only "
"differences are the iterate function, the Jacobian, and the dimension. "
"Both single-IC and ensemble entry points delegate to the generic helpers "
"``_lyapunov_spectrum`` and ``_run_ensemble``."
msgstr ""

